description: This repository contains the code for the AI microservice responsible for predicting personalized workout plans, nutrition recommendation within the GymVietAI application.

name: TaskForge
description: TaskForge - project built on a microservice architecture with Django REST Framework. The platform enables to create groups, assign tasks, track progress. It features JWT authentication, Redis caching, PostgreSQL for data storage, and Cloudinary for image management, showcasing a scalable and modern application design.

name: multi-container-app-deployment
description: This project demonstrates my expertise in deploying and managing multi-container applications using Docker Compose. I've built a scalable web application that combines a Python Flask frontend with a Redis backend, showcasing modern containerization practices and microservices architecture.

name: W4153-Team-Project-UI
description: React UI application for our microservices-based social platform, featuring post creation, hierarchical comments, real-time chat, Google OAuth, AWS S3 for file storage, pagination, and CI/CD pipelines.

name: Carties
description: Carties is a microservices-based web application designed to support car auctions website. Built with a .NET backend and Next.js frontend, the application utilizes Docker, Kubernetes, RabbitMQ, IdentityServer, and Microsoft YARP for service communication, authentication, and real-time updates.

name: SpringBoot2024
description: A Spring Boot application demonstrating RESTful web services, microservices architecture, and database integration. This project showcases essential features like user authentication, CRUD operations, and secure API endpoints. Built with Java, Spring Framework, and JPA for seamless data management.

name: INGSW-Project
description: An Android application developed with Node.js, Express, and Flutter, designed to facilitate real-time online auctions. Users can create listings, place bids, and complete transactions, with a microservices architecture supported by PostgreSQL and Docker containers. Built for the Software Engineering course at the University of Naples "Federico II."

name: react_front_end
description: This project is implemented in React.js and serves as the front-end microservice for the backend repository (https://github.com/mahsahakimi/express_back_end). It is a web application designed for both playing and learning, where teachers can create problems for students, and students can answer them to earn scores.
